OL,4,Cthrilled to be on the trip of a
OL,5,Clifetime
OL,7,FHe's been cleaning the streets of
OL,8,FBeckenham clean since 2017 and has
OL,9,Fbecome a firm favourite with people
OL,10,Fliving there.
OL,12,FBut when residents raised money for
OL,13,FPaul to treat himself and go abroad
OL,14,FPaul's bosses said he couldn't accept
OL,15,Fthe gift because of the terms of his
OL,16,Fcontract.
OL,18,FLuckily, a holiday company stepped in
OL,19,Fand created a competition only Paul
OL,20,Fcould win and he's making the most of
OL,21,Fhis time away.
