OL,4,Cthrilled to be on the trip of a
OL,5,Clifetime
OL,7,F"Me and Paul have a special connection
OL,8,Fbecause he always listens to Elvis and
OL,9,FI'm named Lisa-Marie and it's just
OL,10,Ffollowed on from there," Lisa said.
OL,12,FPaul's employer Veolia said: "We are
OL,13,Fdelighted that Paul can travel to
OL,14,FPortugal for a well-deserved holiday
OL,15,Fthanks to his competition win. To make
OL,16,Fsure he can go and enjoy his holiday
OL,17,Fwhenever he chooses we are giving him
OL,18,Fan extra week of paid leave to enjoy."
